ature in English and a basic reference work that will stimulate research in these areas and help to open up the field to a wider academic readership.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh1 aAndersson, Theodore M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClover, Carol J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrank, Roberta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalinke, Marianne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLindow, John, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLindow, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150174165440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501741654423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501741654/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK